content.description: Another very long, straight single pitch. As close to a 'plaisir' route that I've yet seen, this sweeping route takes up to 16 draws (TBD) before the modern dual-bolt ring anchor mere feet from the top. At a sustained technical 5.8 difficulty it is sure to become popular. For this cliff, anyway.70m rope required to lower or rappel to ground -- the last few feet will even need to be down-climbed. If you only have a 60m, belay from above then rappel down to the Death Ramp and walk down the narrow switch-back to the left (as facing the wall). Wouldn't hurt to knot the ends of your rope!
content.location: Just before reaching the Death Ramp from the access trail, this long bolted route stretches basically straight up the highest cleaned line of the cliff. Starts up out of the trail on an easy inclined face; stays ~20' right of the roof near the top, which is its own route (5.10a).

climbs.name: Vertical Sketchmaster
climbs.fa: Jason Peterson, CS, WS, Paula King 9/91

content.description: A fine route suffering from encroachment on both sides.  Layback the series of vertical left-facing flakes to a bolt.  Move past another bolt to a ramp, run it out slightly over moderate ground to another bolt then move straight up through the crux bulge to easier ground and the anchor.  Six bolts, bring small to medium tri-cams and SLCD's.  Try not to clip the Circling Vultures anchors befor the third bolt or stop there for a nice 5.8 pitch.  Rappel with one rope to cold shuts or bring a second rope.
content.protection: Draws, small to medium tri-cams and SLCD's.
content.location: Right of Line of Cold Shuts #2.

content.description: Follow an aesthetic right facing corner system to a small roof.  Make cruxy moves over roof to flakes.  Continue on face past bolt to rappel anchor.
content.location: Right of I'm a Frayed Knot

content.description: Little beta until climbed personally. Moderate sport route. Climb the start of Weakened Warrior, then climb diagonally right to separate anchor.
content.location: Roughly 20' right of the Death Ramp, shares start with Weakened Warrior.

content.description: The longest of three face climbs right of the Variety Pack corner. More details once climbed personally.
content.location: This is the longest face climb just left of the Death Ramp and Chick McNugget.

content.description: Straight face climb with a cruxy overlap.
content.location: This is the middle of three face climbs to the right of the Variety Pack corner (~100' left of the Death Ramp)

content.description: Little beta until climbed personally. Moderate sport route with roof just before anchor.
content.location: Immediately right of the Death Ramp, just left of Weakened Warrior.

content.description:
A new route not in the Clifton Guidebook. 

  Just to the right of Natural Mystic, closest to the tree adjacent to the cliff is where you'll find Tiers for Walter, easily identified by its two close initial bolts. 

  The moves by the first bolts is the first crux, with a second one coming 2/3rds of the way up. 

  Classic Clifton crystal pinching at it's finest. Can only be climbed with a 60 meter or longer rope.
content.protection:
13 large 1/2" bolts protect the route, but you'll also want some trad pro to slot in the large horizontal cracks and occasional vertical seam along the way. 

  If you climb it without trad gear there are some dangerous run outs.
content.location: The trail with the orange tape and cairns dumps you right at the Left Face in front of natural mystic. Of the cluster of climbs right there this is the left most one, closest to the big tree next to the cliff.

content.description: Not many details available until I climb it myself (posting for a friend). If memory serves, it looks like good rock and meanders slightly on its way up vertical rock, then finishes slightly right above the crown visible from the ground.
content.location: From the trailhead at base of cliff, hike left for several minutes to the far end where bedrock gradually tapers into the ground. Roughly 150' before that point, where routes are 100-120' tall, lies Mike Had to Go Home -- the older sport route full of cold-shuts. about 10' right of Mike is this new sport route, Sunday Candy. There looks to be room for development of an easier route just to the right of these two routes, hint hint...

content.description: To the right of the ramp is a lowered angled face capped with some interesting corners and an overhang.  Take any route to the base of the left-most right-facing dihedral.  Up the corner then move right into a wide down-facing slot.  Finish out the cracks and left to the top.
content.location: Right of Death Ramp.

content.description: Start at the very left end of the wooded ramp and make an awkward mantle onto a shelf eight feet up then face climb past bolts to anchor.
content.location: Right of Circling Vultures.

content.description: The left-most route on the cliff.  Several horizontal breaks.
content.protection: Mixed, some bolts but bring gear.
content.location: First route far left on Left End and Left Face

content.description: Neat face features different than other climbs in the area.
content.location: ~20' left of the Variety Pack corner. Straight up and around features to anchor

content.description: Difficult moves off the ground lead to a line of cold shuts up to flakes then continue through the brown streak.  Seven cold shuts lead to an anchor at 80'.  Stop here or continue past more bolts to a higher anchor.
content.location: Right of Line of Cold Shuts #1.

content.description: Up face following shallow arete.  More face climbing leads to the right past two overlaps and eventually reaches the anchors at 175'.  Nine cold shuts.
content.location: Right of The Black Chick Route.

content.description: Climb a diagonalling line past horizontal cracks towards a broad white streak that is left of a birch tree.
content.location: Right of Mike Had to Go Home.

content.description: Climb straight up just left of the black streak. Anchors are just under the roof.
content.location: Immediately right of the Variety Pack corner.

content.description: Climb the unprotected right leaning 4th class ramp until just before it turns vertical.  Take the left trending bolted line past five bolts and some flakes to the anchor.
content.location: Right of Agony of Defeat

content.description: Directly above the base of the wooded ramp is a dark finger crack at mid height.  1: Wander up the face then up the thin finger crack splitting a face above a tree ledge.  2: Move left up the 5.4 face (no pro) to top.
content.location: Right of Natural Mystic.

content.description: Take the left angling access ramp to the top of the cliff if you desire.  An early route judging by the vintage pins found near the top.
content.location: right of Chick McNugget.

climbs.name: Circling Vultures
climbs.fa: JB, Peter Lataille, Eric Taylor, DN, RG 5/93

content.description: Begin twenty feet right of Vertical Sketchmaster and climb easily through a shallow scoop to a bolt at twenty feet.  Pass 5 more bolts to anchor.
content.location: Right of Vertical Sketchmaster.

content.description: Start on left side of 4th class gully at base of short right facing ramp.  Climb the vertical face past 2 bolts to a spruce tree.  Descend ramp.
content.location: Right of Variety Pack.

content.description: This route begins 150' right of the Death Ramp and just right of some stacked blocks.  Fairly sustained 5.7 climbing but well protected.  Start partway up the Black Beauty ramp.  Face climb up brown face past 3 bolts to ledge then continue over varied face and flakes climbing past 7 more bolts to anchor.  A .5 tri-cam make this climb very safe.
content.location: Right of Scraps.

content.description: Start a step higher along the 4th class ramp, face climbing up the wide brown stain past 7 bolts to the anchor.  Medium gear.
content.location: Right of Ebony and Ivory.

content.description: Begin at base of slightly vegetated narrow ramp and ascend right past 4 bolts. Then climb vertically through flakes and runout slabs past 8 more bolts, finishing the route at massive chains under a small overhang.
content.protection: 8 draws, medium gear for the start.
content.location: Right of Buteo and the Beast.

content.description: Bouldery moves off the ground lead to sustained 5.10 face climbing up the narrow bleached streak passing six well spaced bolts to anchor.
content.location: Right of Black Beauty.

content.description: There are about 17 routes at this wall.
